column5: Lol well done, that is some serious skill
Lol well done, that is some serious skill I would say that is some serious video editing. It did not show him actually hitting the marks. However it does bring a great point across.
That's how I feel most days compared to the other people at the launch...  You know... With a smaller belly if course...
I should do one  mooring the toon. LMAO
Not fun to watch........I really like the idiots that bang into everything while the wife and I are at a boat launch killing some time.

Always amusing to watch the rented pontoon boats come into the locks at Fenelon Falls when the operator has had a 10 minute crash course on how to operate everything associated with boat.  Kind of makes the owners of those mahogany polished yachts a little nervous when pontoon boat comes into the lock sideways with the wind pushing them.
Love the fist pump at the end.....lol.
Awesome, and can relate as I watch some folks at the trailer park who constantly come in hot.
So that's how you dock a boat!  Actually those lake freighters we used to dock at the plant are amazing when they dock. They can put those Iron Islands on a dime.
